50|$|In 1967 Clauss {{was taken}} over by Alco Standard Corporation. Alco Standard, which later {{divested}} its manufacturing companies to create Alco Industries Inc., integrated Clauss into its existing structure to manufacture tools for industrial niche markets. For instance, Clauss made surgical scissors for eye operations, heavy duty metal cutting shears, <b>poultry</b> <b>shears</b> for gutting chickens and specialty items such as anti-acid, anti-magnetic tweezers for the electronics industry.|$|E

